name: IPL Harmony XL Pro Dye VL
description: Dye-VL works using a narrow band of pulsating light, and it is considered a technologically advanced type of IPL laser. IPL stands for Intense Pulse Light. It also can be called Broad Base Light. Like other types of IPL lasers, the treatment works by damaging melanin, or pigment, in the skin to reduce darkened areas. The treatment uses IN-Motion technology to enhance your comfort throughout the treatment. This essentially means that the heat from the laser is applied more gradually compared to other treatments, which results in a noticeably more comfortable procedure. The technician should always do a skin test before proceeding.
care: Avoid sun exposure for a month before and after treatment.
frequency: Every 3 to 4 weeks for 3 to 6 treatments in total.

name: HydraFacial MD®
description: HydraFacial is a refreshing and invigorating treatment to deliver long-term benefits to your skin. This treatment can be tailored to accommodate a variety of skin types for noticeable results. The multi-step treatment entails cleansing, exfoliation, and hydrating with moisturizing serums. This makes HydraFacial a great option for patients with busy schedules who wish to see results without long treatment sessions and downtime. This treatment can last from 4 to 6 weeks.

name: TriPollar® RF technology
description: Radio Frequency energy is a form of electromagnetic energy. Radio Frequency current through tissue will generate heat in the tissue. The science behind TriPollar® is based on the production of collagen and elastin by fibroblast cells in the dermis. When they are heated, two things happen: the elastin contracts and is pulled closer together resulting in immediately tightens skin, while the deep heating effect accelerates collagen regeneration. During the treatment, glycerin is first applied to your skin. Then, the TriPollar® handpiece is used to massage the treatment area. It is during this heated massage that your skin is stimulated to tighten and regenerate–all without vacuuming, suctioning, or skin irritation.
care: No downtime, the skin might be slightly red and warm for a few hours after.
frequency: 4 to 6 treatments every 2 weeks, maintenance every 3 to 6 months afterward.

name: Venus Versa™️
description: It is a light-based technology (IPL combined with advanced SmartPulse™️ technology) to treat both the cause and visible symptoms of acne. The blue light kills the bacteria that cause acne breakouts while the red light reduces the inflammation associated with acne. The advanced real-time cooling system continuously protects the skin from heat. So you get a comfortable treatment that requires no recovery time.
skinType: For all skin types, but darker skins are at a higher risk of discoloration.
care: No downtime, sunscreen is highly recommended.
frequency: 2 treatments per week for an average of 8 to 10 treatments. For maintenance, 2 treatments once a month and once a month afterward. Once the acne clears up, the intervals in between maintenance treatments can be extended.

name: Microneedling eDermaStamp® by Dermaroller®
description: The micro-needling treatment stimulates skin regeneration and reduces wrinkles, scars, hyperpigmentation, melasma and stretch marks. Collagen induction therapy is possibly the most effective method to combat aging skin. The eDermaStamp treatment triggers the natural process of cell regeneration and stimulates the production of collagen fibers, the formation of elastin, improves blood circulation, generates new healthy and new skin cells . This healing process persists and encourages your skin to improve its elasticity and texture. eDermaStamp surgical microneedles will create small bleeding points, this is completely normal. The needle module contains a reservoir that will be filled with ultra-concentrated hyaluronic acid that will be injected into the dermis during the treatment. If you have chosen to treat the pigmentation, the sterile micro-needle reservoir will then be filled with the appropriate medical serum.  The skin repair process will extend over a 12-16 week period after the treatment, and collagen is still restructuring up to 18 months after the treatment.
care: Keep the skin well moisturized, the skin will be red/pinkish and will feel like a moderate to severe sunburn for 12 to 24 hours after the treatment. Avoid all makeup sunscreen, AHA/BHA and other active ingredients for the first 24 hours. Avoid extreme heat and cold for 24 to 48 hours after the treatment.

name: Oxygeneo™
description: A super facial 3 in 1, that exfoliates, oxygenates and nourishes the skin. It can be combined with the Tripollar® and Ultrasound infusion handpieces. Depending on your needs, there are six exclusive treatments using their own Oxypod™ and serums. Glam for sagging skin, Detox for sensitive skin, Hydrate for dry and dehydrated skin, Illuminate for uneven skin tone and pigmentation, Balance for oily and acne-prone skin and Revive for skin rejuvenation and wrinkle reduction.
frequency: Every 2 to 4 weeks until you reach your desired skin goal. Maintenance every few months a year, one treatment can last 4 weeks and are cumulative and will last up to three months afterward.

name: Soprano Titanium
description: The Soprano Titanium is a laser hair removal. One of its biggest advantages compared to the traditionals lasers, is that it is virtually painless. It uses a cooling system that keeps the skin comfortable during the treatment. The cooling system is based on the use of sapphire crystals that keep the skin cool while the laser heats up the hair follicles. This cooling system makes the treatment comfortable, even in sensitive areas like the face and bikini area. It works by using a laser that targets the hair follicle. The laser emits a beam of light that is absorbed by the melanin, or pigment, in the hair. The heat from the laser then damages the hair follicle, which slows down the growth of new hair. Over time, the damaged follicle will produce less hair, resulting in permanent hair reduction. The Soprano Titanium is also unique in that it uses a sweeping motion that allows for more even coverage and faster treatment times. This method of hair removal is safe for all skin types and can be used on any part of the body. This laser has two handpieces, one for bigger regions and one for smaller ones, making it faster and more efficient than most lasers.
skinType: For all skin types, but darker skins might have less apparent results at the end.
care: No sun exposure 4 weeks prior and 2 weeks after your treatment. Avoid sport and heat for 24 to 48 hours after the treatment. Avoid any other method of epilation except for shaving for the duration of your treatment.
frequency: Every 4 to 8 weeks, depending on the body part, for a total of 6 to 12 treatments depending on multiple factors such as age, color of the hair and skin and hormones.

name: Vectus® Laser
description: A brand new last model of Palomar Vectus Diode 810 nm is one of the most powerful lasers on the market today, The Vectus works efficiently on every skin and hair color and even on the fine and fair hair. It features a melanin reader for added safety, sapphire laser tips with advanced Contact Cooling for client comfort, and a large spot size to speed up treatments.
skinType: For all skin types, but darker skins might have less apparent results at the end.
care: No waxing 3 weeks prior, no tanning/sun exposure 3 weeks before and 2 weeks after.
frequency: Every 4 to 8 weeks, depending on the body part, for a total of 6 to 12 treatments depending on multiple factors such as age, color of the hair and skin and hormones.

name: B-Shape T.M.C.
description: The B-Shape T. M.C. is a non-invasive body sculpting treatment that combines the elimination of fat accumulation and the strengthening of muscle mass. The treatment consists of sending direct supramaximal waves to a target area to stimulate muscle contraction. As these waves reach the motor nerves by triggering so-called supramaximal contractions, they also make it possible to reach muscles that are not often solicited. It is also important to know that this technology is a medical one. Therefore, it is safe for your health since the treatment only targets skeletal muscles. The smooth and cardiac muscles are not affected by the waves.
frequency: Minimum of 4 treatments every 2 to 3 days. The results for muscle strengthening will normally appear within 3 days of the first session, and results continue to improve 2 to 4 weeks following the last session. Maintenance every 2 months afterward.

name: TriLipo
description: TriLipo is a non-invasive treatment that harnesses the body’s natural processes for the most effective skin tightening, body contouring, and cellulite reduction results all without destroying a single cell in your body. Artificial destruction of fat cells upsets the body’s natural equilibrium and causes it to compensate by producing new fat cells or expanding existing ones (in other areas of the body). In the long term, it’s likely that the fat, which was unnaturally eliminated, will reappear. TriLipo, on the other hand, works with the body, not against it, to encourage natural fat metabolism and provide unparalleled body contouring results, safely. It targets all four layers of the skin, stimulating collagen production and shrinking fat cells.
frequency: Every 3 weeks for at least 6 treatments.

name: Slimwave
description: Slimwave has 9 selectable programs, which are designed to slim, tone and firm specific areas at the touch of a button delivering 640 possible stimulation changes. Body Sculpting by Slimwave is the most advanced computerized exercise program.  Slimwave Body Sculpt is a form of exercise which is passive.  This treatment uses scientifically and medically approved stimulation to attack fat at the cellular level.  It is safe and fast acting and is a non-invasive, non-surgical treatment that will help you build strong, defined muscles, lose inches and fat, reduce stress, eliminate cellulite and improve circulation.
frequency: 45 minute session, twice a week for about six weeks.
